---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const templates = [
  {
    id: 'general',
    label: 'General — First Response',
    subject: 'Re: Your message to AHoosh',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for reaching out.

I read through what you shared — it makes sense that you're looking at [brief reflection of their situation]. This is exactly the kind of work AHoosh is built for.

Before I put together any thoughts or proposal, it would help to have a short conversation — 20–30 minutes — to understand your situation properly. That way whatever I send back is actually relevant rather than generic.

Are you free for a call this week or early next? Here's my calendar: [Calendly link]

Looking forward to speaking.

Hesam
Founder · AHoosh
contact@ahoosh.ai · ahoosh.ai`,
  },
  {
    id: 'branding',
    label: 'Branding Inquiry',
    subject: 'Re: Branding for [Company]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Good to hear from you. Branding work is something I'm particular about — it's easy to produce something that looks nice but doesn't hold up under business pressure or across channels.

From what you described, it sounds like you need [brand identity from scratch / a refresh / positioning clarity]. The right starting point is usually a half-day positioning session before any visual work begins. That conversation almost always surfaces things the brief doesn't say, and it changes what we end up building.

I'd like to understand more about where you are and what you've tried before. Can we set up a call?

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'website',
    label: 'Website Design & Build',
    subject: 'Re: Website for [Project]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for the message.

Website projects tend to go sideways when the brief skips the strategy layer — when the focus jumps straight to design before the goal, audience, and conversion logic are clear. I try not to work that way.

What I'd want to understand first: what does this site actually need to do? Is this a credibility anchor, a lead generation machine, an e-commerce build, or something else? The answer changes everything about how it should be built.

Can we talk through it? A 30-minute call would let me give you a much clearer picture of what makes sense — timeline, budget range, and approach.

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'marketing',
    label: 'Digital Marketing / Ads',
    subject: 'Re: Digital Marketing',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for getting in touch.

Running ads without a clear conversion funnel is an expensive way to learn what doesn't work. Before I look at channels or budgets, I want to understand what's happening at each step between a stranger seeing your name and becoming a customer — and where that chain currently breaks.

Do you have existing campaigns running? If so, I'd want to look at the data before recommending anything.

Let's talk — even 20 minutes would let me tell you honestly whether we're a good fit and what the right approach looks like.

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'ai',
    label: 'AI Automation / Agent Setup',
    subject: 'Re: AI Setup',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for reaching out.

This area moves fast and there's a lot of noise around it — most people either underestimate what's actually possible or overbuild things that break immediately. I try to find the middle: what can be automated usefully right now, with what you actually have, without creating new problems.

A few questions to think about before we talk:
- What does the workflow or process look like today?
- Where is the bottleneck — speed, consistency, volume, cost?
- What tools or systems are already in place?

30 minutes on a call is usually enough to map out whether there's a clean opportunity here and what it would take to act on it.

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'seo',
    label: 'SEO & Content',
    subject: 'Re: SEO / Content',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Good to hear from you.

SEO without a content strategy is just guessing at keywords. Content without SEO is writing for an empty room. The two have to work together — and both have to connect to what you're actually trying to sell or communicate.

Before I say anything useful, I'd want to see where you currently stand: what's ranking, what content exists, and what the commercial goal behind the traffic is.

Can you share your domain? I'll take a quick look before our call.

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'social',
    label: 'Social Media Management',
    subject: 'Re: Social Media',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for the message.

Social media is one of those areas where being busy and being effective look exactly the same from the outside. The question I always start with: what should social media actually do for this business? Generate leads, build authority, support sales conversations, something else?

The answer changes the platform, the content format, the posting cadence — everything.

Let's talk through it. If we're a good fit, I can outline a realistic plan for what consistent output looks like and what it costs.

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'video',
    label: 'Video Production',
    subject: 'Re: Video Production',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for reaching out.

Before we talk about production — format, length, style — I'd want to understand where this video lives and what it needs to do. A brand film, a product explainer, a talking-head series, and a social ad are four completely different briefs with completely different production approaches.

What are you trying to communicate, and to whom?

If you have examples of videos you like — even outside your industry — send them over. It saves a lot of conversation.

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'pricing',
    label: 'Pricing / Quote Request',
    subject: 'Re: Pricing',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for asking directly — I'll be equally direct.

I don't publish fixed prices because the scope varies too much. A positioning project for a two-person startup looks nothing like the same brief for a 50-person company, and I'd rather give you a number that's right for your situation.

What I can say: most engagements start in the €1,500–€4,000 range depending on depth and deliverables. Strategy retainers start from €800/month. Website builds range from €2,500 for a clean informational site to €8,000+ for complex builds.

To give you a proper quote, I need to understand what you actually need. Can we do a quick call?

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'startup',
    label: 'Startup / Early Stage',
    subject: 'Re: [their subject]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for writing. Building something from scratch is a specific kind of situation — the priorities are different from a company that's already running, and the budget constraints are usually real.

The most valuable thing I can do at your stage isn't necessarily the biggest scope — it's making sure the foundations are right. That means positioning, messaging, and whatever one or two channels you're going to own before you spread thin.

Let's talk about where you are and what the next 90 days should actually look like.

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'enterprise',
    label: 'Established Company',
    subject: 'Re: [their subject]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for the message.

For an organization of your size, the main challenge is usually not a lack of marketing activity — it's that the pieces aren't working together, or there's no clear picture of what's actually driving results versus what's just keeping everyone busy.

I'd want to start by understanding what's already in place before suggesting anything. Could you share a brief overview of your current setup — channels, team, tools — before our call?

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'decline',
    label: 'Polite Decline',
    subject: 'Re: [their subject]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for reaching out and for taking the time to write.

After reading through what you shared, I don't think I'm the right fit for this particular project — [brief honest reason: e.g., outside the areas where I work / better suited to a larger agency / the timing doesn't work].

I wanted to be straightforward rather than drag out a conversation that wouldn't go anywhere useful.

If things change or a different kind of project comes up, feel free to write again.

Best,
Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'after-call',
    label: 'After Discovery Call',
    subject: 'Good speaking with you — next steps',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for the time today. Here's a quick summary of what we covered:

Situation: [one or two sentences on their current state]
Goal: [what they're trying to achieve]
Agreed next step: [proposal / brief / pilot project]

I'll have [the proposal / a detailed breakdown] to you by [date]. If anything changes on your side in the meantime, just let me know.

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'proposal',
    label: 'Sending a Proposal',
    subject: 'AHoosh Proposal — [Project Name]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Attached is the proposal we discussed.

It covers [brief 2-line summary]. I've kept it as concrete as possible — scope, deliverables, timeline, and investment are all in there.

A couple of things worth noting:
- [Key assumption from your call]
- [Optional add-on or phase 2]

Take a look and let me know if anything needs adjusting. If it looks right, we can move forward with [e-signature / a 50% deposit / a kickoff call].

Happy to answer questions on a quick call if that's easier than email.

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'followup',
    label: 'Follow-up (No Response)',
    subject: 'Following up — [original subject]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Just following up on my earlier message — I know things get buried.

Still happy to connect if the timing is right. If the situation has changed or you've gone a different direction, no problem at all — just let me know and I'll close this out.

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'urgent',
    label: 'Urgent Project',
    subject: 'Re: [Urgent project]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Got your message. Understood on the timeline.

A few quick questions before I say whether I can take this on:
- What's the actual hard deadline?
- What exists already that I'd be working with?
- What does "done" look like — what's the output?

Send those over and I'll tell you within a few hours whether this is feasible and what it would cost on a rush basis.

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'referral',
    label: 'Referral from Existing Client',
    subject: 'Re: [their subject]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Great to hear from you — and thanks to [referrer's name] for the introduction.

A referral like this means [referrer] thought there was a real reason for us to talk, so I'll make sure we use the time well.

Can you tell me a bit more about what you're working on? Even a few lines on the situation and what you're trying to figure out would help me come prepared.

[Calendly link]

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'onboarding',
    label: 'Ready to Start',
    subject: 'Let\'s get started — [Project Name]',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Glad we're moving forward on this.

Here's what the next few days look like:

1. [Today/Tomorrow] — I'll send the [contract / brief / invoice] for you to sign/approve
2. [Day X] — Once confirmed, I'll send the onboarding questionnaire
3. [Day Y] — Kickoff call (calendar invite coming)

If you have any existing assets — logos, brand guidelines, old briefs, analytics access — start pulling those together. The more context I have going in, the faster we move.

Looking forward to it.

Hesam`,
  },
  {
    id: 'farsi',
    label: 'Farsi Reply',
    subject: 'پاسخ: [موضوع پیام اصلی]',
    body: `[Name] عزیز،

ممنون که وقت گذاشتید و پیام دادید.

آنچه نوشتید را خواندم. [یک جمله درباره وضعیت آن‌ها]. این دقیقاً نوع کاری‌ست که در AHoosh رویش تمرکز داریم.

قبل از اینکه پیشنهادی بفرستم، ترجیح می‌دم یه مکالمه کوتاه داشته باشیم — ۲۰ تا ۳۰ دقیقه — تا وضعیت رو درست بفهمم.

آیا این هفته یا اوایل هفته بعد برای یه تماس فرصت دارید؟

[Calendly link]

با احترام،
حسام جعفرزاده
AHoosh · contact@ahoosh.ai`,
  },
  {
    id: 'partnership',
    label: 'Partnership Proposal',
    subject: 'Re: Partnership',
    body: `Hi [Name],

Thanks for the note.

Interesting to hear about [their project/company]. I'm generally open to conversations about collaboration when there's a real fit — meaning the work genuinely benefits from both sides being involved rather than one party subcontracting to the other.

Tell me a bit more about what you had in mind specifically. What would the collaboration actually look like in practice?

Hesam`,
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Reply Templates — AHoosh" description="Internal reply templates for AHoosh contact form responses.">

<section style="background:linear-gradient(160deg,#03142E 0%,#010A18 100%);padding:36px 24px 28px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(215,161,61,0.1);">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Internal</div>
    <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-head);font-weight:700;font-size:clamp(20px,5vw,30px);color:var(--silver);margin:8px 0 8px;letter-spacing:-0.01em;">Reply Templates</h1>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--silver-muted);margin:0;">{templates.length} templates · Click any template to copy</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section style="padding:32px 24px 64px;max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;">

  <!-- Filter pills -->
  <div id="filter-bar" style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-bottom:28px;">
    <button class="pill active" data-filter="all" onclick="filterTemplates('all')">All</button>
    <button class="pill" data-filter="general" onclick="filterTemplates('general')">General</button>
    <button class="pill" data-filter="services" onclick="filterTemplates('services')">Services</button>
    <button class="pill" data-filter="process" onclick="filterTemplates('process')">Process</button>
    <button class="pill" data-filter="other" onclick="filterTemplates('other')">Other</button>
  </div>

  <!-- Templates grid -->
  <div id="templates-grid" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;">

    {templates.map((t) => (
      <div class="template-card" data-id={t.id} style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03);border:1px solid rgba(215,161,61,0.1);border-radius:8px;overflow:hidden;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:14px 18px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(215,161,61,0.08);cursor:pointer;" onclick={`toggleTemplate('${t.id}')`}>
          <div>
            <span style="font-family:var(--font-head);font-weight:600;font-size:14px;color:var(--silver);">{t.label}</span>
            <span style="font-size:11px;color:var(--silver-muted);margin-left:12px;">Subj: {t.subject}</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center;">
            <button
              onclick={`copyTemplate(event, '${t.id}')`}
              class="copy-btn"
              data-id={t.id}
              style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold);background:rgba(212,175,55,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(212,175,55,0.25);border-radius:4px;padding:5px 12px;cursor:pointer;white-space:nowrap;"
            >Copy</button>
            <span class="toggle-arrow" id={`arrow-${t.id}`} style="color:var(--silver-muted);font-size:12px;">▼</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="template-body" id={`body-${t.id}`} style="display:none;padding:16px 18px;">
          <pre style="font-family:var(--font-body);font-size:13px;color:var(--silver-dim);line-height:1.75;white-space:pre-wrap;margin:0;">{t.body}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}

  </div>

  <!-- Toast notification -->
  <div id="toast" style="position:fixed;bottom:28px;right:28px;background:#1a2e1a;border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.4);border-radius:6px;padding:12px 20px;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#34d399;opacity:0;transition:opacity 200ms ease;pointer-events:none;z-index:999;">
    ✓ Copied to clipboard
  </div>

</section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pill {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 5px 14px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(215, 161, 61, 0.2);
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--silver-muted);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 150ms ease;
  }
  .pill.active, .pill:hover {
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.4);
    color: var(--gold);
  }
  .copy-btn:hover {
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.18) !important;
  }
</style>

<script>
  const serviceIds = ['branding', 'website', 'marketing', 'ai', 'seo', 'social', 'video', 'pricing'];
  const processIds = ['after-call', 'proposal', 'followup', 'urgent', 'onboarding'];
  const generalIds = ['general', 'startup', 'enterprise'];
  const otherIds   = ['decline', 'referral', 'farsi', 'partnership'];

  function filterTemplates(filter) {
    document.querySelectorAll('.pill').forEach(p => p.classList.remove('active'));
    document.querySelector(`[data-filter="${filter}"]`).classList.add('active');

    document.querySelectorAll('.template-card').forEach(card => {
      const id = card.dataset.id;
      let show = true;
      if (filter === 'services') show = serviceIds.includes(id);
      else if (filter === 'process') show = processIds.includes(id);
      else if (filter === 'general') show = generalIds.includes(id);
      else if (filter === 'other')   show = otherIds.includes(id);
      card.style.display = show ? '' : 'none';
    });
  }

  function toggleTemplate(id) {
    const body  = document.getElementById(`body-${id}`);
    const arrow = document.getElementById(`arrow-${id}`);
    const open  = body.style.display !== 'none';
    body.style.display  = open ? 'none' : 'block';
    arrow.textContent   = open ? '▼' : '▲';
  }

  function copyTemplate(event, id) {
    event.stopPropagation();
    const pre = document.querySelector(`#body-${id} pre`);
    // Temporarily show body to read text if collapsed
    const body = document.getElementById(`body-${id}`);
    const wasHidden = body.style.display === 'none';
    if (wasHidden) body.style.display = 'block';
    const text = pre.textContent;
    if (wasHidden) body.style.display = 'none';

    navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
      const btn = document.querySelector(`.copy-btn[data-id="${id}"]`);
      btn.textContent = 'Copied!';
      setTimeout(() => btn.textContent = 'Copy', 1800);

      const toast = document.getElementById('toast');
      toast.style.opacity = '1';
      setTimeout(() => toast.style.opacity = '0', 2000);
    });
  }
</script>
